00:00:02,180 --> 00:00:07,420
Smoking increases a person's risk of
developing pulmonary emphysema.

3
00:00:07,420 --> 00:00:10,400
In addition, smoking by minors

4
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:16,330
is forbidden because it leads to severe
health issues and nicotine addiction.

5
00:00:16,850 --> 00:00:21,560
Never smoke, even if asked to by others.

6
00:00:23,570 --> 00:00:25,340
...Do you understand?

7
00:01:55,100 --> 00:02:00,770
[Inhale, puff puff... Inhale, puff puff...]

8
00:02:00,770 --> 00:02:05,060
[Hijikata-san, too much smoking is bad for your health.]

9
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:08,180
10 votes in favor, versus 1 against.

10
00:02:08,180 --> 00:02:13,090
Everyone except Hijikata-san voted
in favor, so this bill is approved.

11
00:02:13,090 --> 00:02:15,230
The Shinsengumi headquarters

12
00:02:15,230 --> 00:02:17,780
will no longer allow smoking
in all areas starting today.

13
00:02:17,780 --> 00:02:20,660
H-Hey, the whole headquarters
is going too far.

14
00:02:20,660 --> 00:02:24,300
It's like you're purposely keeping
smokers out of here.

15
00:02:24,300 --> 00:02:27,500
At least make arrangements for
a designated smoking area.

16
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:30,210
What are you saying, Hijikata-san?

17
00:02:30,210 --> 00:02:33,100
Smoking is worse than athlete's foot.

18
00:02:33,100 --> 00:02:37,750
Even though it's not prohibited by
law, nicotine is actually a drug.

19
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:38,600
A drug!

20
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:41,610
Everyday, you inhale and
exhale, inhale and exhale,

21
00:02:41,610 --> 00:02:42,920
you become addicted.

22
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:44,780
So, what's wrong with that?

23
00:02:44,780 --> 00:02:46,630
Even if this is a personal matter for you,

24
00:02:46,630 --> 00:02:48,540
you can't run with this line of argument.

25
00:02:48,540 --> 00:02:54,280
Anyone near a smoker is forced to
become second-hand smokers.

26
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:56,650
But... But...

27
00:02:57,330 --> 00:03:00,850
You're Vice-Chief of the Shinsengumi.

28
00:03:00,850 --> 00:03:02,790
Please think about the other
people around you.

29
00:03:02,790 --> 00:03:06,810
If a Vice-Chief can't even quit smoking
or halt a nicotine addition,

30
00:03:06,810 --> 00:03:10,340
it sets a bad example for everyone else.

31
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:17,050
H-Hey, Harada. You sometimes
smoke, don't you?

32
00:03:17,050 --> 00:03:18,870
Are you all right with this smoking ban?

33
00:03:18,870 --> 00:03:22,570
Yeah...I completely quit smoking,
so it doesn't matter to me.

34
00:03:26,980 --> 00:03:31,090
It's already been decided.

35
00:03:32,010 --> 00:03:36,800
Man, even with Okita-san's proposal,
that was a productive meeting.

36
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:41,180
Yeah. Speaking of smokers,
Vice-Chief was the only one.

37
00:03:41,180 --> 00:03:43,600
It was so smoky and awful in there.

38
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:45,470
My clothes are covered in
that stinky smoke odor.

39
00:03:45,470 --> 00:03:49,190
Any person who practices a martial
art knows smoking is unhealthy.

40
00:03:54,600 --> 00:04:00,600
["Within Each Box of Cigarettes, Are One or Two
Cigarettes That Smell Like Horse Dung"]

41
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:07,240
...gimme a break.

42
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:10,630
Is he seriously intending to keep
me out of the Shinsengumi?

43
00:04:10,630 --> 00:04:15,540
Damn it. I might as well inhale as much
nicotine as possible while I'm outside.

44
00:04:28,870 --> 00:04:31,130
[Smoking on the street is prohibited.]

45
00:04:34,290 --> 00:04:36,260
[BATTLE ROYAL HOST]

46
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:39,430
Ah, excuse me.

47
00:04:39,430 --> 00:04:40,800
Do you have an ashtray?

48
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:47,660
I'm sorry. This restaurant prohibits
smoking in the whole facility.

49
00:04:52,330 --> 00:04:54,770
What's with this city?

50
00:04:54,770 --> 00:04:58,250
Signs everywhere say "No
Smoking," "No Smoking."

51
00:04:58,250 --> 00:05:03,060
I'm sorry, but smoking
isn't allowed in here.

52
00:05:03,060 --> 00:05:04,880
Hey! Your cigarette!

53
00:05:04,880 --> 00:05:07,000
Cigarettes are...

54
00:05:15,450 --> 00:05:17,110
Oh, no! What's he doing?!

55
00:05:17,110 --> 00:05:18,380
Don't stare.

56
00:05:21,060 --> 00:05:24,130
Let me smoke!

57
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:26,490
Damn it.

58
00:05:26,490 --> 00:05:29,270
I didn't even notice but
now I can see there's

59
00:05:29,270 --> 00:05:31,250
no places for us smokers to go anymore.

60
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:34,550
I want to smoke even more
when I'm told not to.

61
00:05:34,550 --> 00:05:41,570
It's hopeless. I can't stand it anymore.
In this situation... I... I...

62
00:05:47,970 --> 00:05:51,720
[SMOKING AREA]

63
00:05:49,580 --> 00:05:51,040
That's it!

64
00:05:53,770 --> 00:05:57,470
I found it! I finally found an oasis!

65
00:05:58,890 --> 00:06:00,460
Here's our next story.

66
00:06:00,460 --> 00:06:04,030
The universal environment
conservation meeting

67
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:06,790
will be held one week from today.

68
00:06:06,790 --> 00:06:11,750
It'll talk about environment-related
issues in the whole universe.

69
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:14,910
And the Bakufu is taking this opportunity
to ask the nation to start thinking about

70
00:06:14,910 --> 00:06:18,100
the environment as it launches the micro-environmental
protection campaign for one week from today.

71
00:06:19,190 --> 00:06:26,370
Let's put aside the big problems of ozone
depletion and global warming.

72
00:06:26,370 --> 00:06:29,160
It's important for each person
to do their own part,

73
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:33,010
no matter how small, to
help the environment.

74
00:06:33,010 --> 00:06:38,790
All your small efforts will start to pile up
into one big push to save the earth.

75
00:06:38,790 --> 00:06:40,110
Yeah, right...

76
00:06:40,110 --> 00:06:45,070
What this old man is trying to say is, before
you go saving the huge Earth...

77
00:06:45,070 --> 00:06:46,740
...you should first save yourself.

78
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:51,360
Someone who can't even save himself
won't be able to save the earth.

79
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:58,770
Someone who can't even save himself
and is disliked by his daughter...

80
00:06:58,770 --> 00:07:01,590
...won't be able to save the earth.

81
00:07:02,700 --> 00:07:05,750
Well, we'll explore all of
that a week from today.

82
00:07:05,750 --> 00:07:07,650
All of Edo...

83
00:07:07,650 --> 00:07:10,200
...will assist in helping implement
the smoking ban.

84
00:07:12,780 --> 00:07:14,490
We repeat.

85
00:07:14,490 --> 00:07:18,940
Currently, an emergency smoking ban
is in effect throughout all of Edo.

86
00:07:18,940 --> 00:07:23,400
Smokers are asked to please throw
away all cigarettes immediately.

87
00:07:23,050 --> 00:07:25,340
Ci...Ciga...rette...

88
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:28,670
Also, please never approach cigarette
vending machines or smoking areas.

89
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:33,010
It'll lead to sever punishment.
We repeat...

90
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,150
Are you taking a trip through
the universe, too?

91
00:07:45,150 --> 00:07:48,610
Man, times are sure changing.

92
00:07:48,610 --> 00:07:52,660
I never thought we'd see the day when
we could travel between planets.

93
00:07:54,020 --> 00:07:56,700
So, which planet are you going to?

94
00:07:57,330 --> 00:07:58,870
[Note: Parody of Planet Namek from Dragon Ball.]

95
00:07:57,330 --> 00:07:58,870
Planet Hamek.

96
00:07:58,870 --> 00:08:02,570
Planet Hamek? There's nothing
to see in that countryside.

97
00:08:02,570 --> 00:08:05,500
It's nothing but tobacco fields.
Why are you going there?

98
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:07,640
...Naturally...

99
00:08:08,280 --> 00:08:10,430
...to smoke some cigarettes!

100
00:08:10,970 --> 00:08:12,880
Don't underestimate a smoker.

101
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:18,310
[Note: Cigarette images were removed from
GinTama manga vol.8 and vol.16 covers.]

102
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:15,580
They claimed the cigarette was edited
out of the manga cover because

103
00:08:15,580 --> 00:08:18,300
I looked like a high
school student smoking.

104
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:21,060
They also said it was never a good
idea to show smokers on the cover.

105
00:08:21,060 --> 00:08:24,060
And they ended up not using
someone smoking.

106
00:08:24,060 --> 00:08:27,050
And we deceptively said it was a pocky chocolate
snack when it was really a cigarette,

107
00:08:27,050 --> 00:08:29,580
or else we'd be forced to give up airing the
show in prime time in North America,

108
00:08:29,580 --> 00:08:32,330
or be stuck with an R rating.

109
00:08:32,330 --> 00:08:35,190
And yet I still haven't given up smoking!

110
00:08:35,790 --> 00:08:39,210
Once the smoking ban starts,
I'll smoke outside Earth!

111
00:08:39,210 --> 00:08:42,690
If cigarettes run out, I'll even
travel to their place of origin!

112
00:08:42,690 --> 00:08:45,990
Don't underestimate a smoker!

113
00:08:48,990 --> 00:08:50,840
I see, I see.

114
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:53,920
I'm so glad to hear that
you came all the way to

115
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:58,510
Planet Hamek to smoke our cigarettes.

116
00:08:58,510 --> 00:09:03,940
Unfortunately, this planet
has been turned into

117
00:09:03,940 --> 00:09:09,310
a scorched field by the evil
emperor, Breeza.

118
00:09:03,940 --> 00:09:09,310
[Note: Parody of Frieza from Dragon Ball.]

119
00:09:09,310 --> 00:09:12,250
So cigarettes are no longer...

120
00:09:17,470 --> 00:09:20,150
This is the last one.

121
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:27,080
Is that all right? Just one...?

122
00:09:29,030 --> 00:09:30,610
Stop it, Grandpa!

123
00:09:30,610 --> 00:09:33,070
Hey, Delde! Take your hands off me!

124
00:09:30,610 --> 00:09:33,070
[Note: Parody of Dende from Dragon Ball.]

125
00:09:33,070 --> 00:09:36,630
That's...! That's the last
cigarette my dad made!

126
00:09:38,270 --> 00:09:41,720
It's a memento of my dad,
who was killed by Breeza.

127
00:09:44,870 --> 00:09:47,460
Dad! Dad!

128
00:09:48,030 --> 00:09:50,180
Dad!

129
00:09:54,450 --> 00:09:56,170
Delde!

130
00:10:36,690 --> 00:10:39,260
...Da...Dad...

131
00:10:49,830 --> 00:10:51,570
Da...! Dad!

132
00:10:51,570 --> 00:10:55,510
Dad!

133
00:11:15,260 --> 00:11:18,490
Dad...

134
00:11:22,330 --> 00:11:25,440
Da... Dad's...

135
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:28,050
Shut up, Delde!

136
00:11:28,050 --> 00:11:30,630
Cigarettes exist to be smoked.

137
00:11:30,630 --> 00:11:33,320
Cigarettes that you can't smoke shouldn't
even be called cigarettes at all!

138
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:36,130
What do you think would please
your father the most?

139
00:11:36,130 --> 00:11:40,340
To let the cigarette get moist in a
drawer or let someone smoke it?

140
00:11:46,210 --> 00:11:49,140
Da...Dad's cigarette...

141
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:51,930
...please enjoy smoking it...

142
00:12:00,750 --> 00:12:03,610
Oh! What a coincidence!

143
00:12:03,610 --> 00:12:08,090
Well, were you able to smoke?
Are you on your way home?

144
00:12:08,090 --> 00:12:09,880
No.

145
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:11,950
What? Where are you going then?

146
00:12:11,950 --> 00:12:14,650
I'm going to defeat Breeza!

147
00:12:14,650 --> 00:12:18,540
Huh? Breeza? What? Aren't
you going there to smoke?

148
00:12:18,540 --> 00:12:20,710
There's no way I can smoke
something like that!

149
00:12:20,710 --> 00:12:21,580
What?!

150
00:12:21,580 --> 00:12:24,300
I'll kill Breeza and smoke afterwards!

151
00:12:24,300 --> 00:12:26,300
He definitely has cigarettes.

152
00:12:26,300 --> 00:12:28,450
Next time, I'll definitely smoke
cigarettes, damn it!

153
00:12:33,070 --> 00:12:36,230
I never suspected that
you were against me.

154
00:12:36,230 --> 00:12:39,830
But I admire your rashness.

155
00:12:52,590 --> 00:12:57,200
Hijikata's quest to smoke
a single cigarette started

156
00:12:52,590 --> 00:13:02,970
[Note: A parody of Master Roshi's
narrations from Dragon Ball.]

157
00:12:57,200 --> 00:13:01,150
because of the Shinsengumi's
smoking ban.

158
00:13:01,150 --> 00:13:02,990
The trip has been full of hardships.

159
00:13:04,910 --> 00:13:07,920
Well, we'll explore all of
that a week from today.

160
00:13:07,920 --> 00:13:12,280
All of Edo will assist in helping
implement the smoking ban.

161
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:17,830
But finally he heads off into the universe.

162
00:13:17,830 --> 00:13:19,290
To smoke some cigarettes!

163
00:13:20,720 --> 00:13:24,650
However, when he arrives
on Planet Hamek,

164
00:13:24,650 --> 00:13:29,170
he finds it was turned into a
scorched field by Breeza.

165
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:41,150
Da...Dad!

166
00:13:41,150 --> 00:13:44,590
Dad!

167
00:13:45,230 --> 00:13:47,700
The young boy Delde's tears...

168
00:13:47,700 --> 00:13:54,480
Hijikata channels his anger into power
and he heads toward the final battle.

169
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:56,760
Hey! Why am I suddenly having flashbacks
of the previous episode?

170
00:13:56,760 --> 00:13:57,900
This isn't Dragon BLEEP!

171
00:13:57,900 --> 00:14:01,220
It's taking too long! I'm in a hurry!
Let's get to the main episode now!

172
00:14:11,250 --> 00:14:14,410
I never suspected that
you were against me.

173
00:14:16,150 --> 00:14:19,310
But I admire your rashness.

174
00:14:22,710 --> 00:14:29,080
But when you see my power, I wonder
if you'll still have the same attitude.

175
00:14:31,170 --> 00:14:33,880
Well, I'll show you.

176
00:14:33,880 --> 00:14:37,200
My full power!

177
00:14:57,080 --> 00:15:02,330
How about that? You look like
you're scared speechless.

178
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:07,940
Get ready for it.

179
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:11,440
Here I come.

180
00:15:15,570 --> 00:15:17,110
Hey, give me a cigarette.

181
00:15:17,680 --> 00:15:19,080
I know you have some.

182
00:15:19,080 --> 00:15:21,840
You destroyed Planet Hamek,
didn't you? Where are they?

183
00:15:22,950 --> 00:15:26,730
I, Breeza-sama, was knocked down
by a monkey like you.

184
00:15:26,730 --> 00:15:30,260
It can't be...you're a legendary
Super Earthling.

185
00:15:26,730 --> 00:15:30,260
[Note: Parody of Super Saiyan from Dragon Ball.]

186
00:15:30,260 --> 00:15:32,220
Shut up, already. Just
give me a cigarette.

187
00:15:32,220 --> 00:15:34,410
I'm grumpy now thanks
to nicotine withdraw.

188
00:15:34,410 --> 00:15:37,980
You're the Super Earthling
who woke up irritated.

189
00:15:37,980 --> 00:15:42,750
Don't tell me you're the
son of that Earthling

190
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:43,940
who was the only one to
challenge me back then?

191
00:15:44,890 --> 00:15:47,090
Huh, who's this? I don't
look nothing like him.

192
00:15:47,090 --> 00:15:48,750
You're totally wrong.

193
00:15:48,750 --> 00:15:52,660
Can it be that you're searching
for the same thing I was?

194
00:15:52,660 --> 00:15:53,560
Huh?

195
00:15:53,560 --> 00:15:56,630
Whatever. I praise you for defeating me,

196
00:15:56,630 --> 00:15:59,200
the emperor of the universe,
so I will give you this.

197
00:15:59,940 --> 00:16:01,700
Here, take it.

198
00:16:01,700 --> 00:16:03,170
That's not what I asked for!

199
00:16:03,170 --> 00:16:05,150
I said, give me some cigarettes!

200
00:16:05,150 --> 00:16:07,570
What's this ball? It's so disgusting!

201
00:16:07,570 --> 00:16:09,380
It's an Ooey-gooey ball.

202
00:16:07,570 --> 00:16:09,380
[Note: Parody of Dragon Ball from Dragon Ball.]

203
00:16:10,020 --> 00:16:11,380
When you collect all seven of those balls,

204
00:16:11,380 --> 00:16:13,040
the Ooey-gooey dragon will appear

205
00:16:13,040 --> 00:16:15,550
and make everything you want
turn Ooey-gooey.

206
00:16:15,550 --> 00:16:16,770
It's a really mysterious ball.

207
00:16:16,770 --> 00:16:19,870
Why Ooey-gooey? I think
you're lying to me!

208
00:16:20,680 --> 00:16:23,010
If there's anything you
want but can't find,

209
00:16:23,010 --> 00:16:28,390
you should collect six more balls
and have your wishes granted.

210
00:16:29,090 --> 00:16:32,340
Hey! Why are you making that kind
of face made by the super villain

211
00:16:32,340 --> 00:16:34,420
right before he dies in the big scene
at the end of the episode?

212
00:16:34,420 --> 00:16:38,680
Anyway, why do I have to do all
of this just to get a cigarette?!

213
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:40,620
Give me a break.

214
00:16:40,620 --> 00:16:42,700
It'll be a lot faster if I just
go to another planet

215
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:44,780
and buy a pack of cigarettes
at a vending machine.

216
00:16:44,780 --> 00:16:48,900
That's right. I should've done
that earlier. I'll go do that.

217
00:16:50,450 --> 00:16:53,880
Grillin! Open your eyes, Grillin!

218
00:16:50,450 --> 00:16:53,880
[Note: Parody of Krillin & Goku from Dragon Ball.]

219
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:56,440
Damn it! If only I had
all the Ooey-gooey balls!

220
00:16:58,660 --> 00:17:00,190
Grillin!

221
00:17:04,040 --> 00:17:07,460
...Hey, what are you doing?

222
00:17:07,460 --> 00:17:10,700
I'm trying to revive Grillin.

223
00:17:10,700 --> 00:17:12,650
Who the heck is Grillin?!

224
00:17:12,650 --> 00:17:14,430
You came to smoke some
cigarettes, right?

225
00:17:14,430 --> 00:17:15,890
And who's that sitting right next to you?!

226
00:17:15,890 --> 00:17:18,630
Yo! I'm Kobayashi! I'm so excited!

227
00:17:15,890 --> 00:17:18,630
[Note: Parody of Goku and
Yamcha from Dragon Ball.]

228
00:17:18,630 --> 00:17:21,130
Kobayashi?! I'm not excited
about that name at all!

229
00:17:21,130 --> 00:17:23,170
[Note: Refers to Bulma from Dragon Ball.
She dated Yamcha in the series.]

230
00:17:21,130 --> 00:17:23,170
You're Bulma's ex-boyfriend,
aren't you?

231
00:17:23,170 --> 00:17:24,610
Shut up!

232
00:17:24,610 --> 00:17:28,250
You know, Grillin might
have some cigarettes!

233
00:17:28,250 --> 00:17:31,160
I'll definitely smoke next time, damn it!

234
00:17:35,650 --> 00:17:37,580
[Note: Parody of Cell from Dragon Ball.]

235
00:17:35,650 --> 00:17:37,580
I'm Celo!

236
00:17:39,140 --> 00:17:40,840
That's enough! You're so persistent.

237
00:17:40,840 --> 00:17:42,060
I know it's going to take a long time.

238
00:17:42,060 --> 00:17:45,420
I get bored easy. Hey, just give me
some balls. You have some, right?

239
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:50,330
Why? Why does he have
so much power?

240
00:17:50,330 --> 00:17:51,000
Shut up!

241
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:54,630
Hurry up and give me some balls so I can
revive Grillin and smoke a cigarette.

242
00:17:54,630 --> 00:17:59,480
I can't believe I lost after taking
cells from the Super Earthling...

